We ve been hard at work on some major features behind the scenes. We re diligently working to build test them and bring you an even better Ripl experience. Stay tuned for future updates! In the meantime we invite you to download the latest version and get ready to create stunning content with Ripl! Update today and let your creativity shine with Ripl! As always we appreciate your feedback and support as we continue to improve our app. If you have any questions or feedback or need assistance please reach out to our support team at feedback ripl.com.

We re excited to bring you the latest update for Ripl packed with fantastic templates to make your 4th of July celebrations even more memorable. In this release we re introducing a range of brand new templates specifically designed to capture the spirit of Independence Day. Now you can create stunning and patriotic content that will truly stand out! Bug fixes Performance improvement With this update we ve also worked hard to squash pesky bugs that may have been causing any disruptions. We ve also implemented various performance improvements to ensure a smoother and more seamless user experience. Thank you for being a part of the Ripl community and we can t wait to see what you ll create next! If you have any questions feedback or need assistance please reach out to our support team at feedback ripl.com.

This update adds two features to help you pick the perfect color for your posts: Saved Colors: Want to use the same color as your last post In the top right corner of the color picker we ll display the 4 colors you ve used most recently. Hex Color Codes: Have a specific brand color you want to use Just type in the hex code at the bottom of the color picker and we ll find it for you!

Now when you save creations to Camera Roll they will also be added to a Ripl album in your Photos. This will make it easy to find all of your Ripl posts without having to scroll through the 43 selfies you took at the Beyonce concert last weekend.

Sometimes life feels like you re endlessly uploading something and it just won t post. We can t help with that. If you ever run into problems let us know at feedback ripl.com and we ll make sure it s fixed faster than a clogged toilet at a plumbing conference.

This update fixes some minor bugs that snuck in with the 1.5 update. New in 1.5: Multi Photo Animated Posts: Choose up to 4 photos to include in an animated background for your post. Ripl Pro Trial: Want to see if Ripl Pro is right for you or your business without dropping any cold hard cash Start a free 7 day trial now available for all Ripl users in the app menu. Bug Crash Fixes

Ever spent hours staring at your Camera Roll trying to decide which photo to use in your Ripl post Same. So we added the option to have the background of your animated post cycle through up to 4 photos! Or if 1 photo is your thing you can keep doing that. No pressure. This update also includes: Ripl Pro Trial: Want to see if Ripl Pro is right for you or your business without dropping any cold hard cash Start a free 7 day trial now available for all Ripl users in the app menu. Bug Crash Fixes

This update fixes a bug in version 1.4.3 that caused new Ripl Pro subscribers to not immediately gain access to Pro features. New in 1.4.3: A bunch of you asked about editing previous posts sharing them again. Now you can! For any posts created after this update just tap them in My Posts and hit the share arrow. You ll be able to make changes to the design and post it again! This update also includes: Turn Off Link Shortening: Want your links to display exactly how you add them Turn off s.ripl.com link shortening in Account Settings. You can now double tap to edit text or images while customizing your post! We also added more customization options to many designs as part of our never ending quest to help you create the perfect post. This update also includes: Re sharing a post from My Posts will now copy the caption from the previous share Option in Ripl Pro Settings to turn off link shortening in post captions Note: This will also turn off click tracking in your post engagements Bug fixes

We know. Sometimes you create a post so mind blowingly awesome that sharing it once just isn t enough. With this update click any post in My Posts and you ll have the option to share it again! This update also includes: A fix for a bug that caused Ripl to crash for some users Other minor fixes and improvements
This update includes: Improvements to Instagram posting Behind the scenes work to get ready for new features Fixes for some minor bugs
This update includes: Minor bug fixes performance improvements

This update: Fixes a bug that prevented some users from sharing their posts on Facebook Fixes a bug that prevented some Ripl Pro users from restoring purchases We re extremely sorry if you experienced either of these issues. You can contact us with feedback or questions anytime at feedback ripl.com!
This update includes: A fix for a freezing issue that some users may be experiencing Other minor bug fixes performance improvements

Introducing the Ripl PRO Design Catalog the place to discover and download new eye catching designs for your posts. Ripl PRO members can download and use as many designs as they want with new options added weekly! If you haven t upgraded yet try out the catalog by downloading and posting with our rotating daily FREE design. This update also includes: Improved text customization: Tap text while customizing your post to use new resizing and layout tools Disconnect Accounts: Accidentally connect the wrong social media account Fix the issue under Account Settings in the app menu New font options and color schemes Bug fixes performance improvements

Just a few bug fixes this time but stay tuned for more exciting updates coming soon. In the meantime we d love to hear how we can make Ripl better for YOU. Just shoot us an email at feedback ripl.com!

Introducing a new feature for Ripl Pro members: Post Scheduling! Set a date time you want your Ripl post to go out and we ll handle the rest. This update also includes: Option to delete posts from the My Posts feed New Post Designs Bug Fixes Performance Improvements

Posting a Link is back! On the Create a Post screen click Add destination link then either paste your link in or find it using our easy built in tool. Your post will automatically pull in the link photos details. Easy right Ripl Pro is also growing! It now includes: Removing the Ripl logo and link from your posts Adding your own custom logo or image to posts Saving posts to your Camera Roll ...and more new features coming soon! This update also includes new layouts and bug fixes. Send us your thoughts at feedback ripl.com!
Introducing Ripl Pro! Remove the Ripl logo from all your posts with a simple one time purchase. This update also includes: New Layouts including additional Holiday styles Minor Improvements Bug Fixes

The Ripl elves have been hard at work and added new holiday post layouts. Spread some cheer on your social media! This update also includes: Notifications when people engage with your Ripl posts Minor Improvements Bug Fixes Send feedback questions or holiday gifts to feedback ripl.com!

You asked we answered: Now share Ripl posts on Facebook Pages for your business brand or blog! This update also includes: New Animated Post Templates Minor Improvements Bug Fixes We d love to hear from you. Send feedback or questions to feedback ripl.com!

A HUGE thanks to everyone that has tried Ripl and sent feedback over the past few weeks! This update includes: Share as GIF: Share your Ripl posts on Facebook Twitter as animated GIFs because everyone loves GIFs Save to Camera Roll: Option to save your posts so you can share them wherever and however you want! Pinch to Zoom Cropping: While customizing a post pinch to zoom in and showcase a specific part of the image Other Improvements: Streamlined the posting experience fixed a Twitter formatting issue and some other small bugs Send us feedback or questions anytime at feedback ripl.com!

The first Ripl update! A few bugs managed to sneak by us in v1.0 so we exterminated those and broke out the polish in a few other areas of the app. More importantly send us any thoughts feedback or concerns to feedback fanzo.me!
